<span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Now available:&nbsp; Three Expanded Batch Wizard Options on Accurint&reg; for Insurance</span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">On November 18, 2010, Batch Wizard options in Accurint for Insurance will be expanded to include batch processes for Social Security Numbers, Date of Birth and Date of Death.&nbsp; These options can be used for processing data files of up to 200,000 records and can be selected independently or combined as a group.&nbsp; These new options will drive more flexibility and efficiency into your ability to easily process large groups of records while delivering the information that facilitates faster claims decisions. </span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />

	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Pricing for these new batch enhancements:</span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Date of Death- $.05 per input record plus $.60 per DOD returned</span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Date of Birth- $.15 per DOB returned or verified</span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Social Security Number- $.35 per SSN returned or verified</span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />

	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">LexisNexis&reg; Risk Solutions also has many secure batch processing solutions that can be customized to meet your requirements for larger batch input files; please contact your Account Manager for more details.&nbsp; </span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">New Police Records Functionality Enables Easier Access and Workflow</span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Accurint&reg; for Insurance features new functionality that enables Police Records orders to be accessed and shared among Accurint for Insurance users within your organization.&nbsp; This new enhancement makes your organization's Police Records orders available for access by another team member who needs to utilize the information while processing a claim.&nbsp; This is enhancement is designed to reduce duplicitous research and efforts within your team's research workflow and increase a work team's speed in completing comprehensive claims research. </span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />

	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">This enhancement can also be applied to Police Records orders already in queue; please have your Account System Administrator contact Accurint Customer Support at 1.866.277.8407 for more details.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">NEW CONTENT IN DRIVER LICENSES SEARCH</span> </span><br style="font-family: Arial;" />
	<br style="font-family: Arial;" />
